The paper deals with the consensus problem in multi-agent systems, which is a topic in the field of control theory and networked systems. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.SY (Systems and Control). The paper also proposes distributed protocols for achieving consensus, which falls under the category of multi-agent systems (cs.MA). The use of switching directed topology is a common technique in distributed systems and graph theory, which suggests the category cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) as a likely choice. The paper also mentions the use of analysis techniques and performance analysis, which are common in the fields of machine learning and artificial intelligence, suggesting the categories cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) and cs.LG (Machine Learning) as possible choices.
